    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cardiovascular-modeling-group",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. The CFD model demonstrates sufficient credibility to support the COU decision (identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions, RH < 1 criterion). A known limitation exists in the turbulence model performance at the low-flow, high-speed edge case (31% NIH over-prediction), which is acknowledged in the output comparison factor rationale. This limitation does not affect the primary decision-relevant operating points. The overall credibility evidence supports acceptance of the model for the stated COU. Risk is acceptable.",
